The paper deals with the problem of brain matter segmentation from MR images using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves the use of a hybrid deep learning network, which combines both supervised and unsupervised learning techniques, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of texture and vesselness features also suggests relevance to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method on MRI scans suggests relevance to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
